text.tspan: United States: COVID-19 weekly death rate by vaccination status, All ages
Death rates are calculated as the number of deaths in each group, divided by the total number of people in this
group. This is given per 100,000 people.
Note: The mortality rate for the 'All ages' group is age-standardized to account for the different vaccination
rates of older and younger people.
Data source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, Vaccine Breakthrough/Surveillance and Analytics Team
